records.addlTxt: Signed by Judge Reilly
Motion to forfeit bail granted.

9:53 AM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing.  Prosecuting attorney Shawn N Woller in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Tyler B Yonke not in court.  Attorney Justin G Griffis in court for Tyler B Yonke.  Court takes a brief recess at 9:54 a.m.  Case recalled at 9:56 a.m.; all appearances remain the same.  Atty. Griffis attempted to call the defendant and was not able to get ahold of him.  Atty. Griffis has no explaination for his client's non-appearance.  Court notes a capias was authorized and stayed until today's date due to a missed court appearance on 8/22/2022.  Based on the non-appearance today Capias to issue and court orders bail be forfeited.
Plea/sentencing hearing on August 26, 2022 at 09:30 am.

3:01 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing.  Prosecuting attorney Andrew Nesheim in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Justin G Griffis in court for Tyler B Yonke.  Defendant Tyler B Yonke not in court.  Atty. Griffis advises that his client contacted him and is not able to make the hearing today due to transportation issues.  Atty. Griffis requests that the court stay a capias and if possible adjourn to this Friday for plea and sentencing.  State presents statements, they are requesting a capias be issued and bail be revoked and/or forfeited.  Court will authorize but stay the issuance of a capias and will adjourn to this Friday, 08/26/2022, for plea and sentencing.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 26, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Effective August 1, 2022, this case is assigned to Branch 7 Judicial Vacancy, pursuant to 22-SO-04(67).
Plea/sentencing hearing on August 22, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

11:21 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Tyler B Yonke in court with attorney Justin G Griffis.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Julian Marrufo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Griffis provides an update, he is asking the matters be set for plea and sentencing in about 30-45 days.  Court adjourns for plea and sentencing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 22, 2022 at 02:30 pm.
Hearing on July 11, 2022 at 10:00 am.

02:03 PM Defendant Tyler B Yonke in court, in custody, with State Public Defender Law Intern for attorney Justin G Griffis.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense states the defendant had written down the incorrect date and time for himself for the previous court date.  State would not object to reinstating bail at this time.  Court quashes warrant, reinstates bail and sets matter before the Trial Court.  Hearing scheduled for July 11, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Waukesha County Public Safety Assessment Report filed by Wisconsin Community Services.

10:51 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Attorney Justin G Griffis in court.   Defendant Tyler B Yonke did not appear.   Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Griffis has attempted to contact his client but has not hear back from him, and he does not know why the defendant has not appeared today.  State requests a capias and bail be revoked and/or forfeited.  Atty. Griffis request the capias be stayed until the end of business day today.  Court to issue a capias and orders bail be forfeited.
